  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nWhen a payload is fetched from the payload cache it is permanently removed, meaning that it may not be able to be fetched again.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/693886b94176faa4cb450f024696cb69cda2fe58/beacon_node/execution_layer/src/lib.rs#L375-L378\r\n\r\nI think this is most relevant for local blocks which have been blinded and stored in the cache, but it could also apply to blocks from relays which can't be re-fetched after a deadline.\r\n\r\n## Expected Behaviour\r\n\r\nRe-fetching a payload is of dubious usefulness, but it might be useful in redundant setups or for distributed validators. It would be a minor change to leave the cache entry intact after serving the payload, and rely on the LRU mechanism to evict it. The only downside would be a `clone` instead of a move.",
